@eloyhernandez4025I think it’s because he’s probably closely associated with the production of it regardless before all of it, so no longer working with him means they would have to cancel the show as it is basically too closely connected to him?
I also think because of how honestly disgusting his actions were it’s hard for a lot of people to separate the art from the artist which is completely reasonable, 
you can argue all you want but at the end of the day it does matter how a work is perceived with people, as the author is directly connected to it no matter what anybody does so it doesn’t really diminish that association
